[FILE:261:descriptions/desc.primary]
Hickory-DNS (formerly "Trust-DNS") is an authoritative DNS server. Its 
main distinguishing feature from other Open-Source nameserver software is 
that Hickory is written in 100% safe Rust. It supports DNSSEC and already 
implemented most of the relevant RFCs.


[FILE:323:descriptions/desc.utils]
This subpackage contains the utilities that come with Hickory-DNS:

* recurse: CLI interface for hickory-dns-recursor
* resolv: CLI interface for hickory-resolver (a lookup tool similar to 
host)
* dns: CLI interface for hickory-client (providing query functionality 
similar to dig as well as subcommands to manage zones)


